00:56:27.470 --> 00:56:31.100
realize what those
operators describe.

00:56:31.100 --> 00:56:33.730
So I gave you the example for
the displacement operator.

00:56:45.780 --> 00:56:47.860
When I learned about
the beam splitter,

00:56:47.860 --> 00:56:51.250
and its underlying
physics, there

00:56:51.250 --> 00:56:54.540
was one thing which
really fascinated me.

00:56:54.540 --> 00:56:59.560
And this is the most simple
element you can think of.

00:56:59.560 --> 00:57:02.250
I mean, what is simpler
than a beam splitter?

00:57:02.250 --> 00:57:05.550
A beam splitter has two
inputs, two outputs.

00:57:05.550 --> 00:57:09.410
The simplest optical element
is just an attenuator.

00:57:09.410 --> 00:57:11.480
Put in a window
in your laser beam

00:57:11.480 --> 00:57:14.650
and you lose 4% of
your power preserves.

00:57:14.650 --> 00:57:16.920
Or put in just a little
bit of dirty optics

00:57:16.920 --> 00:57:18.770
and you lose a few percent.

00:57:18.770 --> 00:57:20.630
So what I want to
discuss with you now

00:57:20.630 --> 00:57:24.125
is, what really is an
attenuator quantum mechanically?

00:57:28.890 --> 00:57:35.710
Well if, classically,
the attenuator

00:57:35.710 --> 00:57:37.930
would do the following.

00:57:37.930 --> 00:57:43.180
An attenuator is a device
which has a transmission, which

00:57:43.180 --> 00:57:45.270
is a transmission
coefficient squared,

00:57:45.270 --> 00:57:46.990
which is smaller than unity.

00:57:49.810 --> 00:57:54.910
And, in a classical system,
if you have a coherent state,

00:57:54.910 --> 00:58:00.805
you would simply assume that the
coherent state gets multiplied

00:58:00.805 --> 00:58:02.320
by the transmission coefficient.

00:58:05.010 --> 00:58:17.300
In other words, that you
have your original state,

00:58:17.300 --> 00:58:20.880
described by this
phase, or alpha.

00:58:20.880 --> 00:58:25.430
And then, the action
of the attenuator

00:58:25.430 --> 00:58:35.420
would simply be to
scale everything down

00:58:35.420 --> 00:58:38.620
by a transmission
effect of alpha.

00:58:38.620 --> 00:58:40.750
So the picture you should
have is the following.

00:58:40.750 --> 00:58:42.320
You have a coherent state.

00:58:42.320 --> 00:58:45.400
It gets attenuated by the
transmission coefficient.

00:58:45.400 --> 00:58:48.940
But if there are fluctuations
about the coherent state,

00:58:48.940 --> 00:58:51.140
also the fluctuations
get attenuated.

00:58:51.140 --> 00:58:55.450
Because everything gets
attenuated by this attenuator.

00:58:55.450 --> 00:59:00.960
So if you look at that, you
should immediately say, no.

00:59:00.960 --> 00:59:03.180
This is quantum
mechanically forbidden.

00:59:03.180 --> 00:59:07.160
Because a coherent state with
a minimum uncertainty state,

00:59:07.160 --> 00:59:11.170
this shaded area cannot
be smaller than 1/2.

00:59:11.170 --> 00:59:13.600
But here it has become smaller.

00:59:13.600 --> 00:59:15.770
So what I've shown
to you here is

00:59:15.770 --> 00:59:18.480
it's a violation of
quantum mechanics.

00:59:21.620 --> 00:59:25.190
It would actually mean, let
me just give you the example.

00:59:25.190 --> 00:59:40.520
It would mean that if-- yeah.

00:59:43.860 --> 00:59:45.600
The coherent state
is quantum limited.

00:59:45.600 --> 00:59:48.080
And if you calculate what is
the fluctuations in the photo

00:59:48.080 --> 00:59:49.580
number, it's a shot noise.

00:59:49.580 --> 00:59:53.970
So just to give you sort of
simple, intuitive example,

00:59:53.970 --> 00:59:59.460
if you have 10,000 photons plus
minus 100, it's a shot noise.

00:59:59.460 --> 01:00:00.680
Square root n.

01:00:00.680 --> 01:00:03.740
If you could now attenuate
it by a factor of 100,

01:00:03.740 --> 01:00:08.050
and you would go from
10,000 plus minus 100,

01:00:08.050 --> 01:00:11.910
to 100 plus minus 1.

01:00:11.910 --> 01:00:13.790
That's much better
than the shot noise.

01:00:13.790 --> 01:00:15.560
I mean, this is what
I'm just telling you

01:00:15.560 --> 01:00:18.040
what a simpleminded
attenuator would do.

01:00:18.040 --> 01:00:20.590
And you would immediately say,
that's too good to be true.

01:00:20.590 --> 01:00:22.550
I cannot get sub
shot noise light.

01:00:26.640 --> 01:00:27.490
So what is wrong?

01:00:34.060 --> 01:00:34.740
Impossible.

01:00:34.740 --> 01:00:37.060
Not allowed.

01:00:37.060 --> 01:00:40.820
Well, we've just tried
to formulate something

01:00:40.820 --> 01:00:41.730
intuitively.

01:00:41.730 --> 01:00:42.820
And we have to be careful.

01:00:47.320 --> 01:00:55.740
Well, we know
already one way how

01:00:55.740 --> 01:01:00.362
we can attenuate an input beam.

01:01:00.362 --> 01:01:04.300
And maybe we should go back to
the situation and analyze it.

01:01:04.300 --> 01:01:08.570
We know what if we can attenuate
it with a beam splitter.

01:01:08.570 --> 01:01:12.850
And this beam splitter has a
transmission coefficient of t.

01:01:12.850 --> 01:01:17.260
And then we get our
transmitted coherent light.

01:01:17.260 --> 01:01:21.720
There is something
getting reflected.

01:01:21.720 --> 01:01:26.820
But now we realize that
this beam splitter is not

01:01:26.820 --> 01:01:29.480
just a device which
has one input.

01:01:29.480 --> 01:01:31.060
It has another input.

01:01:31.060 --> 01:01:34.600
And you may say, well, I don't
care about the other input.

01:01:34.600 --> 01:01:36.340
I don't want to use it.

01:01:36.340 --> 01:01:39.890
Well, if you don't
want to use the input,

01:01:39.890 --> 01:01:41.620
it has the vacuum state.

01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:51.110
So therefore, if you would
realize the attenuator

01:01:51.110 --> 01:02:00.110
with the beam splitter, it
would mean that, in addition,

01:02:00.110 --> 01:02:03.190
and this is what the math
really shows, in addition

01:02:03.190 --> 01:02:07.140
to the attenuated coherent
state, which mathematically

01:02:07.140 --> 01:02:12.350
is also attenuating
the fluctuations,

01:02:12.350 --> 01:02:16.240
you have to add something.

01:02:16.240 --> 01:02:19.750
Which is the
reflection coefficient

01:02:19.750 --> 01:02:22.945
times the vacuum state.

01:02:27.880 --> 01:02:30.120
Which is this.

01:02:30.120 --> 01:02:35.370
And if you now
correctly do the math,

01:02:35.370 --> 01:02:40.960
if you add the two
together, you find

01:02:40.960 --> 01:02:50.730
you get a coherent state which
has an amplitude of t alpha.

01:02:50.730 --> 01:02:53.510
But has the correct
[INAUDIBLE] fluctuation

01:02:53.510 --> 01:02:55.960
is again a minimum
uncertainty state.

01:02:55.960 --> 01:02:58.900
So the disk of your
attenuated state

01:02:58.900 --> 01:03:01.780
hasn't exactly the same area
as the unattenuated state.

01:03:05.830 --> 01:03:08.700
So I've shown you
the physical part.

01:03:08.700 --> 01:03:11.220
I have shown you the
graphical solution.

01:03:11.220 --> 01:03:12.700
The math is very simple.

01:03:12.700 --> 01:03:15.300
But I really want you
to do the math yourself.

01:03:15.300 --> 01:03:16.730
This is a new
homework problem we

01:03:16.730 --> 01:03:19.065
designed to illustrate
the physics.

01:03:19.065 --> 01:03:21.630
But what it tells
you is the following.

01:03:21.630 --> 01:03:25.370
If you take a neutral
density filter out

01:03:25.370 --> 01:03:28.340
of the lab [INAUDIBLE] and say,
this is not a beam splitter.

01:03:28.340 --> 01:03:30.230
This is an attenuator.

01:03:30.230 --> 01:03:31.290
Sorry.

01:03:31.290 --> 01:03:35.500
You cannot simply attenuate
a quantum mechanical mode.

01:03:35.500 --> 01:03:38.500
This is not a unitary
time evolution.

01:03:38.500 --> 01:03:42.130
What you attenuate [INAUDIBLE]
is, without you knowing it,

01:03:42.130 --> 01:03:45.590
it couples the electromagnetic
wave to whatever.

01:03:45.590 --> 01:03:47.790
To the heat path
of the [INAUDIBLE],

01:03:47.790 --> 01:03:49.180
which is in your attenuator.

01:03:49.180 --> 01:03:50.950
I don't even want
to describe it.

01:03:50.950 --> 01:03:53.820
But you're not
circumventing the limitation

01:03:53.820 --> 01:03:55.160
of the beam splitter.

01:03:55.160 --> 01:03:58.630
Whenever you attenuate,
whenever you have a laser beam,

01:03:58.630 --> 01:04:01.480
and it undergoes losses,
when you send a laser beam

01:04:01.480 --> 01:04:04.370
through the atmosphere, and
it undergoes some losses by,

01:04:04.370 --> 01:04:06.180
who knows,
[INAUDIBLE] scattering

01:04:06.180 --> 01:04:10.085
through the air or
something like this.

01:04:10.085 --> 01:04:13.670
That means you get an
attenuated coherent state.

01:04:13.670 --> 01:04:16.960
But you couple in the
fluctuations off the vacuum.

01:04:16.960 --> 01:04:19.810
And this establishes
shot noise now,

01:04:19.810 --> 01:04:22.750
at the lower level of intensity.

01:04:22.750 --> 01:04:27.780
So your attenuator is not
a single state device.

01:04:27.780 --> 01:04:29.010
Dissipation.

01:04:29.010 --> 01:04:32.110
Attenuation really
means you connect

01:04:32.110 --> 01:04:33.850
with other parts of
[INAUDIBLE] space.

01:04:33.850 --> 01:04:39.520
You cannot attenuate in a
small part [INAUDIBLE] space.

01:04:39.520 --> 01:04:40.650
This is impossible.

01:04:40.650 --> 01:04:42.300
This is not unitary
time evolution.

01:04:57.620 --> 01:05:05.320
So what I've just told you
has dramatic consequences

01:05:05.320 --> 01:05:11.560
for any form of non
classical, or squeezed, light.

01:05:11.560 --> 01:05:14.370
And that's the following.

01:05:14.370 --> 01:05:16.030
Most of you are
experimentalists.

01:05:16.030 --> 01:05:19.930
And you know that when you run
a laser at one or two watts,

01:05:19.930 --> 01:05:23.560
you send it through optics, and
shudders, and optical fibers.

01:05:23.560 --> 01:05:26.780
How much do you get at the
end of your experiment?

01:05:26.780 --> 01:05:28.560
Not even 50%.

01:05:28.560 --> 01:05:31.300
So, whenever you create
light, and then you

01:05:31.300 --> 01:05:34.570
want to do something, you
lose some of the light.

01:05:34.570 --> 01:05:39.060
And let's now assume that
you have done what was really

01:05:39.060 --> 01:05:43.550
a breakthrough in scientific
headlines within your lifetime.

01:05:43.550 --> 01:05:46.230
You have generated
squeezed light.

01:05:46.230 --> 01:05:48.790
And now we want to use
the squeezed light.

01:05:48.790 --> 01:05:51.642
Shine it on atoms and do
a precision measurement,

01:05:51.642 --> 01:05:53.600
which is better than the
standard quantum limit

01:05:53.600 --> 01:05:55.183
because you have
squeezed the ellipse.

01:05:55.183 --> 01:05:58.420
And you want to now exploit
the sharpness of the ellipse.

01:05:58.420 --> 01:06:02.560
What happens to your
aspect ratio of the ellipse

01:06:02.560 --> 01:06:05.900
when your beam is attenuated?

01:06:05.900 --> 01:06:09.180
So let me just discuss
it with you graphically.

01:06:09.180 --> 01:06:11.920
So let's assume we
have a squeezed state.

01:06:11.920 --> 01:06:13.720
And we send it through
an optical fiber.

01:06:18.020 --> 01:06:20.210
The result is you will
never send a squeezed state

01:06:20.210 --> 01:06:21.310
through an optical fiber.

01:06:21.310 --> 01:06:23.170
But I want you to realize that.

01:06:23.170 --> 01:06:27.001
So let's assume we have our
squeezed state, symbolized

01:06:27.001 --> 01:06:27.500
by that.

01:06:32.260 --> 01:06:34.620
Let's use some red
color for the state.

01:06:34.620 --> 01:06:37.240
And now, in the
time evolution, we

01:06:37.240 --> 01:06:40.180
have some [INAUDIBLE]
scattering.

01:06:40.180 --> 01:06:41.840
Some fiber absorption.

01:06:41.840 --> 01:06:43.930
But you know already,
the absorption

01:06:43.930 --> 01:06:47.310
is in reality a beam splitter,
which happens in the vacuum.

01:06:47.310 --> 01:06:47.810
So

01:06:47.810 --> 01:06:51.620
We have now some finite
transmission coefficients.

01:06:51.620 --> 01:06:56.300
And that would mean,
which is the bad news,

01:06:56.300 --> 01:07:00.940
that your ellipse gets shrunk.

01:07:00.940 --> 01:07:01.440
It shrinks.

01:07:08.680 --> 01:07:12.040
It shrinks by the
transmission factor t.

01:07:14.590 --> 01:07:17.890
But that's what I did bad.

01:07:17.890 --> 01:07:19.240
You lose some of your power.

01:07:19.240 --> 01:07:28.150
But the really bad thing
is that if I multiply it

01:07:28.150 --> 01:07:38.045
with the reflection coefficient,
you couple in the vacuum.

01:07:38.045 --> 01:07:38.545
Oops.

01:07:38.545 --> 01:07:41.030
I'm going to change to red.

01:07:44.900 --> 01:07:49.750
And, as a result, since
the noise in the vacuum

01:07:49.750 --> 01:07:52.620
is equal in both
quadrature components,

01:07:52.620 --> 01:07:56.980
you've worked so hard to squeeze
it, to make it asymmetric.

01:07:56.980 --> 01:08:01.550
But what you get now
is from your ellipse,

01:08:01.550 --> 01:08:06.060
you get something which is
much more egg shaped now.

01:08:06.060 --> 01:08:10.520
So in other words, you can
write it down with operators.

01:08:10.520 --> 01:08:12.970
But once you understand
what is going on,

01:08:12.970 --> 01:08:21.100
you immediately realize that
losses reduce the squeezing.

01:08:24.750 --> 01:08:28.090
And this is a challenge to
all the experiments using

01:08:28.090 --> 01:08:29.760
squeezed or non classical light.

01:08:34.580 --> 01:08:36.810
And you see how
the scaling works.

01:08:36.810 --> 01:08:39.529
If you have squeezed your
ellipse by a factor of 100,

01:08:39.529 --> 01:08:44.729
even 1% of the vacuum
will spoil your squeezing.

01:08:44.729 --> 01:08:47.100
So the more you have
squeezed, the more

01:08:47.100 --> 01:08:52.149
non-classical the light is--
the more valuable it is.

01:08:52.149 --> 01:08:55.660
The more sensitive it is,
to even very small losses.

