01:10:35.610 --> 01:10:37.260
What I want to
explain to you, here,

01:10:37.260 --> 01:10:41.310
is the physical concepts
behind teleportation,

01:10:41.310 --> 01:10:46.150
and you the crucial steps
to realize teleportation.

01:10:46.150 --> 01:10:47.685
So first, what is teleportation?

01:10:50.460 --> 01:10:55.600
Well, teleportation has
a sender and a received,

01:10:55.600 --> 01:10:57.750
which in quantum
information science

01:10:57.750 --> 01:10:59.183
are called Alice and Bob.

01:11:01.780 --> 01:11:07.850
Teleportation means Alice
has a quantum state, psi.

01:11:07.850 --> 01:11:12.630
And she wants to send this
quantum state, psi, to Bob.

01:11:12.630 --> 01:11:16.250
In other words, you have,
maybe, some squeezed light.

01:11:16.250 --> 01:11:18.170
You have something--
a quantum state,

01:11:18.170 --> 01:11:21.760
psi-- which is interesting.

01:11:21.760 --> 01:11:33.100
And the question is, how can
Bob create an identical copy

01:11:33.100 --> 01:11:35.094
of this quantum
state, psi, that he

01:11:35.094 --> 01:11:37.260
can sort of [INAUDIBLE]
with the same quantum state.

01:11:40.810 --> 01:11:43.320
Before you appreciate
teleportation,

01:11:43.320 --> 01:11:47.880
you have to realize
what the problem is.

01:11:51.550 --> 01:11:55.890
The problem is, really,
in fundamental properties

01:11:55.890 --> 01:11:58.610
of quantum systems,
fundamental limitations-- what

01:11:58.610 --> 01:12:00.600
you can do with
a quantum system.

01:12:00.600 --> 01:12:03.530
First, I have to tell you
what is allowed, and what not.

01:12:03.530 --> 01:12:06.940
In this game, teleportation
means, of course,

01:12:06.940 --> 01:12:10.660
you will not take your atom and
your photons in the state psi,

01:12:10.660 --> 01:12:13.160
just propagate them to
Bob, and Bob has them.

01:12:13.160 --> 01:12:14.340
That's trivial.

01:12:14.340 --> 01:12:16.780
I can send any
quantum state to you

01:12:16.780 --> 01:12:20.070
by transmitting an atom
or a laser beam to you,

01:12:20.070 --> 01:12:22.900
and you have the same
quantum state I had earlier.

01:12:22.900 --> 01:12:24.250
This is not teleportation.

01:12:24.250 --> 01:12:27.010
This is trivial propagation.

01:12:27.010 --> 01:12:30.483
What is meant is that we don't
have a quantum channel-- I'm

01:12:30.483 --> 01:12:33.350
not allowed to send my
quantum state to you.

01:12:33.350 --> 01:12:36.560
But in teleportation, I can do
a measurement on the quantum

01:12:36.560 --> 01:12:41.030
state, call you up through
a classical communication

01:12:41.030 --> 01:12:43.380
channel, and tell you, the
result of my measurement

01:12:43.380 --> 01:12:45.310
is such and such.

01:12:45.310 --> 01:12:47.610
And then you would say, well,
if I have a spin system,

01:12:47.610 --> 01:12:50.810
and I measure spin up--
I call you and say,

01:12:50.810 --> 01:12:54.510
my measurement was spin up, and
you create a spin up system.

01:12:54.510 --> 01:12:57.110
Isn't that teleportation?

01:12:57.110 --> 01:13:00.460
The answer is no, because
maybe the state I had

01:13:00.460 --> 01:13:02.710
was a superposition
of spin up and down.

01:13:02.710 --> 01:13:05.300
And what I measured
is only spin up.

01:13:05.300 --> 01:13:07.220
And by telling you
it's spin up, you

01:13:07.220 --> 01:13:08.950
would never create a
superposition state,

01:13:08.950 --> 01:13:10.690
you would just create
a spin up state.

01:13:10.690 --> 01:13:14.900
So the effect is, that if I
do a measurement on my quantum

01:13:14.900 --> 01:13:17.325
state, and report
my results to you,

01:13:17.325 --> 01:13:20.280
you have insufficient
information.

01:13:20.280 --> 01:13:23.150
Because a projective
measurement on a quantum

01:13:23.150 --> 01:13:27.650
state inevitably leads
to loss of information.

01:13:27.650 --> 01:13:30.180
A measurement on a
single quantum state

01:13:30.180 --> 01:13:32.240
does not create
enough information

01:13:32.240 --> 01:13:33.630
to recreate the quantum state.

01:13:36.540 --> 01:13:39.830
Of course, there is
an obvious solution.

01:13:39.830 --> 01:13:42.580
When we want to obtain
information about a quantum

01:13:42.580 --> 01:13:45.830
state, we often, in
quantum mechanics,

01:13:45.830 --> 01:13:48.210
have to do many measurements.

01:13:48.210 --> 01:13:50.410
And we can take a
spin state, we can

01:13:50.410 --> 01:13:52.160
measure what is
its x, what its y,

01:13:52.160 --> 01:13:54.440
what is the c
component of the spin.

01:13:54.440 --> 01:13:56.750
We can completely
characterize the spin state,

01:13:56.750 --> 01:13:58.720
and then we know
everything about it.

01:13:58.720 --> 01:14:02.040
But the problem is, we have
only one quantum state,

01:14:02.040 --> 01:14:04.884
and we can't do
repeated measurements.

01:14:04.884 --> 01:14:07.300
Then you would say, well, the
next thing is, why don't you

01:14:07.300 --> 01:14:10.030
just take your quantum
state and Xerox it,

01:14:10.030 --> 01:14:11.347
make many, many copies.

01:14:11.347 --> 01:14:12.930
And then you have
an ensemble, and you

01:14:12.930 --> 01:14:15.210
can take as many
measurements you want.

01:14:15.210 --> 01:14:17.840
You can do an x
measurement, p measurement.

01:14:17.840 --> 01:14:20.650
I mean, you can reconstruct
the complete wave function.

01:14:20.650 --> 01:14:22.640
You can measure with an x basis.

01:14:22.640 --> 01:14:24.800
You can measure with
a momentum basis.

01:14:24.800 --> 01:14:27.320
You can collect all
the information.

01:14:27.320 --> 01:14:30.900
But the problem is-- otherwise
the whole teleportation

01:14:30.900 --> 01:14:32.475
would not be an
issue at all-- there

01:14:32.475 --> 01:14:34.490
is the no-cloning theorem.

01:14:34.490 --> 01:14:38.160
You cannot duplicate
a quantum state.

01:14:38.160 --> 01:14:41.930
If you have an atom in a certain
quantum state and another atom,

01:14:41.930 --> 01:14:44.250
it is quantum-mechanically
forbidden--

01:14:44.250 --> 01:14:46.670
there is no unitary
transformation,

01:14:46.670 --> 01:14:49.590
no way of creating a
situation that you have

01:14:49.590 --> 01:14:53.500
one unknown quantum
state, plus another atom,

01:14:53.500 --> 01:14:57.120
or another light beam,
and after some interaction

01:14:57.120 --> 01:14:59.300
you have two times the
same quantum state.

01:14:59.300 --> 01:15:00.400
You cannot clone.

01:15:03.620 --> 01:15:08.335
Therefore, based on all that, we
cannot clone the quantum state.

01:15:08.335 --> 01:15:10.540
We are only left
with the one copy

01:15:10.540 --> 01:15:12.830
of the quantum state,
which Alice has.

01:15:12.830 --> 01:15:14.877
Alice is not allowed
to send it to Bob.

01:15:14.877 --> 01:15:16.710
Maybe Bob is on the
other side of the ocean,

01:15:16.710 --> 01:15:19.150
or on another planet.

01:15:19.150 --> 01:15:22.610
All what Alice can do is,
she can do one measurement

01:15:22.610 --> 01:15:27.010
and tell Bob, this
is my measurement.

01:15:27.010 --> 01:15:29.980
So this is the problem
of teleportation.

01:15:29.980 --> 01:15:32.890
How is that possible?

01:15:32.890 --> 01:15:37.790
Well, the way how I put
it, it seems impossible.

01:15:37.790 --> 01:15:41.360
But there's a way out of it.

01:15:46.210 --> 01:15:47.770
Let me just write
down what I said.

01:15:47.770 --> 01:16:01.630
So the goal is now-- Alice
performs measurement,

01:16:01.630 --> 01:16:06.780
reports result to Bob.

01:16:16.810 --> 01:16:28.030
And now, Bob will recreate
the quantum state.

01:16:28.030 --> 01:16:31.600
What I've just said is, to
perform a single measurement

01:16:31.600 --> 01:16:32.760
is not enough information.

01:16:32.760 --> 01:16:34.490
So this is not enough.

01:16:34.490 --> 01:16:36.680
We need one more resource.

01:16:36.680 --> 01:16:45.610
And the resource,
which is now used

01:16:45.610 --> 01:16:55.850
to use quantum teleportation,
is that you take some entangled

01:16:55.850 --> 01:17:02.630
system, or-- and this why I talk
about it today-- or squeezed

01:17:02.630 --> 01:17:04.874
light.

01:17:04.874 --> 01:17:05.790
That's the same thing.

01:17:05.790 --> 01:17:09.630
It's a form of entanglement.

01:17:09.630 --> 01:17:13.410
I told you that when we
generate squeezed light

01:17:13.410 --> 01:17:15.620
with a parametric
down conversion,

01:17:15.620 --> 01:17:20.890
the parametric down conversion
takes a green photon

01:17:20.890 --> 01:17:24.570
and creates two identical
infrared photons.

01:17:24.570 --> 01:17:26.560
Until now, we have
discussed that

01:17:26.560 --> 01:17:29.170
those identical
infrared photons go

01:17:29.170 --> 01:17:31.650
into the same mode,
which is squeezed.

01:17:31.650 --> 01:17:34.440
But now, a slight
extension of this concept

01:17:34.440 --> 01:17:37.410
would mean, in parametric
down conversion,

01:17:37.410 --> 01:17:40.490
you squeeze something, but
one photon goes to Alice,

01:17:40.490 --> 01:17:41.450
one photon goes to Bob.

01:17:47.990 --> 01:17:53.930
So now, Alice and Bob have
an additional resource.

01:17:53.930 --> 01:17:57.280
They sort of own--
each of them-- half

01:17:57.280 --> 01:18:00.970
of the two twin brothers,
which are the photons created

01:18:00.970 --> 01:18:03.050
in the parametric down
conversion process.

01:18:05.900 --> 01:18:09.240
And that will work.

01:18:14.740 --> 01:18:15.980
So the idea is the following.

01:18:19.890 --> 01:18:24.190
To create those twin
beams of photons

01:18:24.190 --> 01:18:29.020
is simply done with an
optical parametric oscillator.

01:18:29.020 --> 01:18:31.755
There is one extension, which
is described on the Wiki.

01:18:31.755 --> 01:18:33.380
I won't have time to
explain it to you.

01:18:33.380 --> 01:18:36.080
But it's a two-mode OPO.

01:18:36.080 --> 01:18:39.210
It puts the two identical
photons-- not in the same beam,

01:18:39.210 --> 01:18:41.270
as we did before, we had
the a dagger squared,

01:18:41.270 --> 01:18:47.470
a squared operator-- they
go into two different modes.

01:18:47.470 --> 01:18:50.300
You know the magic of
beam splitters by now.

01:18:50.300 --> 01:18:51.960
Now, two beams come out.

01:18:51.960 --> 01:18:55.470
One goes to Alice,
one goes to Bob.

01:18:55.470 --> 01:19:00.640
If Alice would take her input
state-- this unknown state

01:19:00.640 --> 01:19:06.580
which is handed to her
by Victor, somebody

01:19:06.580 --> 01:19:10.030
else who participates in
the game-- we know already,

01:19:10.030 --> 01:19:14.160
if Alice would
perform a measurement,

01:19:14.160 --> 01:19:16.200
the quantum state
would be destroyed.

01:19:16.200 --> 01:19:19.830
The result of the measurement--
let's talk about spin-1/2--

01:19:19.830 --> 01:19:21.420
would only be one
spin projection.

01:19:24.220 --> 01:19:28.600
It's not enough to
reproduce a state.

01:19:28.600 --> 01:19:31.270
But what she is doing
is, she uses, again,

01:19:31.270 --> 01:19:33.330
the magic of the beam splitter.

01:19:33.330 --> 01:19:36.170
So one of those
twin brother photons

01:19:36.170 --> 01:19:38.650
is now mixed with
the unknown quantum

01:19:38.650 --> 01:19:41.110
state at the beam splitter.

01:19:41.110 --> 01:19:45.390
And the output of
the beam splitter

01:19:45.390 --> 01:19:49.040
is now entering the
balanced homodyne detection,

01:19:49.040 --> 01:19:51.270
which we just discussed.

01:19:51.270 --> 01:19:53.320
The output of this beam
splitter-- and there

01:19:53.320 --> 01:19:56.300
are two outputs--
both of them is now

01:19:56.300 --> 01:19:59.040
becoming part of a balanced
homodyne measurement.

01:19:59.040 --> 01:20:00.670
And you see the ingredients.

01:20:00.670 --> 01:20:02.900
So this, and this,
will be measured.

01:20:02.900 --> 01:20:04.800
The other input for
the balanced homodyne

01:20:04.800 --> 01:20:08.120
is a strong local oscillator.

01:20:08.120 --> 01:20:10.720
The phase of the
local oscillator

01:20:10.720 --> 01:20:14.810
is chosen, in one case, that you
measure the x or a 1 quadrature

01:20:14.810 --> 01:20:18.280
component, or the p
or the a 2 component.

01:20:18.280 --> 01:20:21.490
So now what Alice
has done is, by using

01:20:21.490 --> 01:20:24.060
this balanced
homodyning, she has--

01:20:24.060 --> 01:20:26.730
with this local
oscillator-- has actually

01:20:26.730 --> 01:20:29.430
now performed two measurements.

01:20:29.430 --> 01:20:34.070
The quantum state is destroyed,
but here she gets an x value,

01:20:34.070 --> 01:20:35.345
and here she gets a p value.

01:20:38.560 --> 01:20:40.340
So how the magic works out.

01:20:40.340 --> 01:20:44.270
It's really just a few
lines of mathematics, now.

01:20:44.270 --> 01:20:48.170
These were sort of, you
know, twin brothers.

01:20:48.170 --> 01:20:50.610
But it wasn't clear
in which quantum

01:20:50.610 --> 01:20:52.712
state the twin brothers are.

01:20:52.712 --> 01:20:54.212
If you write it
down, and I can show

01:20:54.212 --> 01:20:56.850
you the formula in a moment,
these are twin brothers.

01:21:00.570 --> 01:21:06.790
But those twin brothers-- this
is Brother 1, this is Brother

01:21:06.790 --> 01:21:12.680
2-- are in sort of a
continuum of states.

01:21:12.680 --> 01:21:16.480
And when Alice this would
measure that this twin brother

01:21:16.480 --> 01:21:20.930
is in state big X, that would
be a projective measurement.

01:21:20.930 --> 01:21:24.490
And Bob's twin brother
would now, with certainty,

01:21:24.490 --> 01:21:28.570
also be in the state, X.

01:21:28.570 --> 01:21:34.460
So therefore, what happens
is, the measurement of x and p

01:21:34.460 --> 01:21:38.270
is now producing-- is now,
through the measurement

01:21:38.270 --> 01:21:43.760
process-- putting the other
photon, or the other beam,

01:21:43.760 --> 01:21:46.690
the other twin brother, into
a specific quantum state.

01:21:49.780 --> 01:21:53.280
And if you look for
few lines of math,

01:21:53.280 --> 01:21:57.210
the magic is that the quantum
state-- which is now here,

01:21:57.210 --> 01:22:03.620
with Bob-- turns out
to be a displaced copy

01:22:03.620 --> 01:22:06.070
of the original state.

01:22:06.070 --> 01:22:09.930
And the displacement
depends on x and p.

01:22:09.930 --> 01:22:14.750
So if Alice now tells Bob,
hey, I measured x and p,

01:22:14.750 --> 01:22:20.170
and Bob is now [INAUDIBLE]
his displacement operator--

01:22:20.170 --> 01:22:21.670
remember, a
displacement operator is

01:22:21.670 --> 01:22:26.910
nothing else than an
unbalanced beam splitter,

01:22:26.910 --> 01:22:30.300
with a huge local
oscillator as an input.

01:22:30.300 --> 01:22:35.300
So if Bob is now setting up
his displacement operator,

01:22:35.300 --> 01:22:38.210
it makes a displacement
which depends on x and p.

01:22:38.210 --> 01:22:43.270
He can take this other twin
brother, shift it back,

01:22:43.270 --> 01:22:46.530
and he will exactly
regenerate the quantum

01:22:46.530 --> 01:22:50.050
state which Alice had.

01:22:50.050 --> 01:22:52.830
So this is, now,
how a quantum state

01:22:52.830 --> 01:22:57.024
can be transmitted
without having any quantum

01:22:57.024 --> 01:22:58.065
channel for transmission.

01:22:58.065 --> 01:23:00.380
You're not propagating
the quantum state.

01:23:00.380 --> 01:23:04.380
You use classical communication,
but the resource you use

01:23:04.380 --> 01:23:07.130
is some EPR pairs,
or squeezed light.

